Looking for a quick and tasty midweek dinner option? Try cooking up our Creamy Miso Mushroom Rigatoni in just 20 minutes for a delicious and speedy meal.

== Pasta ==

Boil a full #kettle{}. Pour the boiled water into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{1/2%tsp} on high heat.

Add the @rigatoni pasta{180%g} and bring back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back in the pan. Drizzle with @oil{drizzle} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

== Mushrooms ==

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #frying pan{} on high heat.

When hot, add the @sliced mushrooms{120%g} to the pan.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and fry until browned, ~{5-6%minutes}, stirring occasionally.

== Aromatics ==

In the meantime, peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Roughly chop the @chives{1%bunch}(roughly chopped) (use #scissors{} if easier).

Once the mushrooms have browned, add the garlic to the pan and cook for ~{1%minute} more.

== Sauce ==

Stir in the @water for the sauce{150%ml}, @miso paste{15%g} and @wild mushroom paste{15%g}.

Bring to the boil then lower the heat and simmer until thickened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

== Assembly ==

Once the sauce has thickened, stir in the @creme fraiche{150%ml} and @grated hard italian style cheese{40%g}. Simmer for ~{1%minute}.

Add the @baby spinach{40%g} to the pan a handful at a time until wilted and piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir in the cooked pasta, @butter{20%g} and half the chives.

Taste and season with salt and pepper if needed. Add a splash more water if you feel it needs it.

== To Serve ==

Share the creamy miso pasta between your #bowls{}.

Finish by sprinkling over the remaining chives. Enjoy!